he final medal standings.\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1868, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"atie\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1824}, {\"ngram\": \"44th placein\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"the final medal standings\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1867}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Africa finished inthirdplace among the 12 African countries which won medals in Paris.\", \"from\": 1870, \"to\": 1962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1870, \"end\": 1882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.4676092905031595e-15, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1956, \"end\": 1961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.1978996973442458e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"inthirdplace\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1904}, {\"ngram\": \"the 12 African countries\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 1952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatjana Smithwas the 'big' winner for South Africa, collecting gold in the women's 100m breaststroke and silver in the women's 200m breaststoke.\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 2108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2002, \"end\": 2014, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.4676092905031595e-15, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tatjana\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 1971}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'big' winner\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 1997}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2031}, {\"ngram\": \"m breaststr